{"type":"message","id":"c827b591","parentId":"6050f4c4","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:44:41.951Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Assessing Initial Assumptions**\n\nI'm now diving into the user's initial assumptions. The user seems to think the UI's markdown files are compact, and suspects \"Skills\" is the main space hog. My focus is on validating or challenging these preliminary beliefs before moving forward.\n\n\n**Pinpointing the Culprit**\n\nI've confirmed the user's suspicion; the workspace markdown files are minimal. It's the `<available_skills>` block containing numerous 'feishu-*' skills that's bloated. This is where I'll focus my efforts to reduce the token load and optimize the system.\n\n\n**Identifying Key Bloat Sources**\n\nI'm now identifying the key causes of the token bloat. The excessive `<description>` tags within each skill are a significant issue, particularly the numerous 'feishu-*' skills and their detailed descriptions. The user's focus on \"Skills\" and \"Feishu\" is spot on; the files in the workspace are indeed lightweight. The native tool schemas are also worth noting.\n\n\n**Proposing Removal Strategies**\n\nI am now focusing on concrete solutions. If the user doesn't actively use the OpenClaw-Lark extension, removing it is the most significant step. This eliminates nine bloated skills instantly. Other skills, like \"claude-delegate\" and \"weather,\" can also be removed if unneeded. I'm exploring commands like `openclaw skills list` to manage and remove these skills, or formulating a simple user-facing guide. I can use `exec` to perform removal or output instructions.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3fd67d088641301a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -l ~/.openclaw/extensions/ && ls -l ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/ && ls -l ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-h